A bachelor’s degree or above in Biology, Biochemistry, Biotechnology, Biomedical Science, Microbiology, Pharmacology, or other discipline related to life science;
Minimum 2 years of relevant experience in life science or biomedical research laboratory; Less experience with higher qualification will also be considered;
A proven practical experience in operation of flow cytometer, sequencer or confocal microscopy would be preferred;
Keep abreast of the latest development in instrumentation and analytical methods;
Familiar with occupational hazards and standard safety practices;
Customer-centered service attitude with strong problem-solving skills is a must;
A good team player with excellent communication, analytical, interpersonal and presentation skills as well as able to work independently;
Proficient in MS office (Words, Excel and PowerPoint); and
Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese.

